<br>
1 gnome (in pices)<br>
2 Cans of Cream of Gnome (this can be substituted with cream of chicken of gnome cant be found)<br>
2 Hand full of mushrooms sliced<br>
2 cans of sliced water chestnuts<br>
2 cans of large black olives<br>
2 sticks of butter<br>
2 sprigs of thyme<br>
3 clove of garlic<br>
<br>
In a frying pan melt the 2 sticks of butter till just turning brown.<br>
Add your Gnome, make sure it is well cleaned .. <br>
Fry until brown and crisp on all sides.<br>
<br>
Remove gnome from pan and set aside.<br>
In pan add the 2 can of creamed gnome stir till smooth, add in all the other ingredients and bring to a soft boil.. <br>
<br>
IN a casserole dish, add Gnome to bottom and smother with the above cream sauce.  On the top sprinkle fresh parley.<br>
<br>
Cook for 45 min in a 250 Degree oven (or till gnome is cooked completely)<br>
<br>
Serve over white rice and with a deep red wine.. <br>
